The paper discusses the formal analysis of security protocols, which falls under the category of "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses statistical techniques to infer the secrecy guarantees provided by a security protocol, which falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the validation of implementations of security protocols, which falls under the category of "cs.SE" (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions process-calculi, which falls under the category of "cs.PL" (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper discusses the probabilistic model checking technique, which falls under the category of "cs.SY" (Systems and Control).
